\section{Results}\label{sec:results}
In the 34 sources searched, we discovered six new MSPs (see Table~\ref{tab:results}). Pulse profiles from the discovery observations are shown in Figure~\ref{fig:pulses}. The rotation periods range between 1.99 and 4.66 ms, and their DMs span 17--65\,pc $\textnormal{cm}^{-3}$. Orbital solutions have been obtained for all new discoveries from initial timing observations. However, phase-connected timing solutions (including precise positions, period derivatives, spin-down luminosities, and a study of the gamma-ray properties of the coincident gamma-ray sources)  are not yet available for most of the MSPs, and will be presented elsewhere. A study of the redback {PSR~J1048$+$2339}{} is presented in \cite{den15}.

